<br>
Well, first of all we all know Charm is broke (admitted by Verant).  But, this experience have to be told.  Yesterday, Im in a group in BOT and a mini-boss is up.  We had 5 members so we invited a guildmate (65 Enchanter) even though we had a enchanter already.  On our way to kill the mini-boss we invis up and proceed to where he is. A air elemental can see through invis and started killing everyone...and got adds.  First the Tank, then the 62 Enchanter, then cleric...next me.  After I finish loading which took for ever (assumed a wipe), I started running back to BOT so we can try again. But wait, the 65 Enchanter &quot;SOLOED&quot; the mini-boss and took on a extra mob.<br>
<br>
Now, yes this might sound like envy but in all reality its a shame.  Verant nerfed &quot;Quad&quot; kiting within a week of finding out about its use.  But how long has it taking to put charm at a level to not make it overpowered?  For any other spell Verant wouldve just reduced its power a long time ago.<br>
<br>
Now, I truly know why alot of Enchanters solo and dont want a group.  A ring dropped off of mob and a Spectral Parchment.  Not bad.<br>
<br>
BTW, the Enchanter is a good person, and he did random the Parchment. I believe the ring poofed because he had gotten some more adds.<br>
<br>
<br>
Immlazen<br>
<br>
